# vidgen

Agent-first video automation repository.

## Human Quickstart
- Architecture: `ARCHITECTURE.md`
- Agent map: `AGENTS.md`
- Product specs: `docs/product-specs/index.md`
- Execution plans: `docs/PLANS.md`

## Current Scope
- YouTube OAuth channel check: `scripts/youtube_check.js`
- YouTube resumable upload CLI: `scripts/youtube_upload.js`
- Payload-driven upload wrapper: `scripts/youtube_upload_from_payload.js`

## Required Env Vars
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`
- `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET`
- `YOUTUBE_REFRESH_TOKEN`

Optional:
- `YOUTUBE_DEFAULT_PRIVACY`
- `YOUTUBE_DEFAULT_CATEGORY_ID`
- `YOUTUBE_MADE_FOR_KIDS`

## Quality Gates
- `node scripts/openclaw_topology_check.js`
- `node scripts/check_knowledge_base.js`
- `node scripts/doc_gardener.js`
- `node scripts/security_preflight.js`
- `node scripts/pipeline_orchestrator_dry_run.js`

## VPS Auto Sync (OpenClaw)
Primary mode (event-driven from GitHub Actions):
1. Add repository secrets:
   - `VPS_HOST`
   - `VPS_USER`
   - `VPS_SSH_KEY`
   - optional: `VPS_PORT`
2. Install service on VPS (timer disabled by default):
   - `bash /docker/openclaw-jnqf/data/repos/vidgen/scripts/install_vps_autosync_systemd.sh`

Run once manually:
- `bash /docker/openclaw-jnqf/data/repos/vidgen/scripts/vps_autosync_openclaw.sh`

Optional fallback timer (hourly):
- `ENABLE_TIMER=1 bash /docker/openclaw-jnqf/data/repos/vidgen/scripts/install_vps_autosync_systemd.sh`
- `systemctl status vidgen-openclaw-autosync.timer --no-pager`

Service logs:
- `journalctl -u vidgen-openclaw-autosync.service -n 200 --no-pager`
